The SANDF has received allegations of torture by Mzansi soldiers in the DRC.SANDF chief Lieutenant-General Solly Shoke is reported to have opened an investigation into the allegations.The SANDF also said that they had been alerted to the reports of torture and assault GBH which were allegedly committed by SA soliders that were deployed under the UN in the DRC.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>The allegations have been viewed in a very serious light, Shoke said, and that the investigation will serve to determine their genuineness.The investigations will be done by national investigating officers who will be working with the DRC.“General Shoke has emphasised that ill-discipline and criminality will not be tolerated within the ranks of the SANDF and those found to have transgressed the code of conduct and military disciplinary code will be dealt with without fear or favour,” SANDF spokesperson Brigadier-General Mafi Mgobozi is reported to have said.